content:
The Prediction Examination tab allows you to interact with model metrics and see how they stack up against actual outcomes in the training data.

In Performance, click Prediction Examination. The table displays a random sample of 100 rows of data (observations) in the CRM Analytics dataset used to train the model. Columns represent columns in the training dataset.

Select a row to display details about the prediction that the model generated for that observation:

METRIC	DESCRIPTION
Predicted Outcome	Outcome that the model predicted.
Actual Outcome	Outcome that actually occurred.
Ranked Probabilities	Chart of classes with the probability of each outcome.
Top factors	Features that have the biggest contribution to the outcome.

SEE ALSO: Metrics for Multiclass Classification Use Cases.
title: Understanding Prediction Examination in Multiclass Classification
